==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sibilation
<hw>Sib`i*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sibilatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>Utterance with a hissing sound; also,
the sound itself; a hiss.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He, with a long, low <qex>sibilation</qex>, stared.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sibilatory</ent>⟦br⟧
